// @check
// @error operator '+' is not defined for i32 and string
// FIXED (was a parked soundness xfail, ROADMAP A13). `add`'s params are inference holes; a `+` on
// a hole operand DEFERS its form to the call site (a hole is permissively assignable to string AND
// numeric). The call site now re-validates the deferred binary-op constraint under the SUBSTITUTED
// argument types: `add(1, "x")` resolves the constraint to `i32 + string`, which the emitter cannot
// lower, so it is a clean type error instead of a silent garbage `0` / invalid module. The same one
// rule rejects `s + "!"` over a number and `a + b` over `(i32, string)`, and accepts every valid
// monomorphic shape (i32+i32, string+string, f64+f64).
function add(a, b) a + b

print(add(1, "x")) // REJECTED: i32 + string is not addable
